        "id": "policy_reception",
        "name": "Policy: Front Desk Reception Rotation",
        "subject": "REVISED WEEKLY RECEPTIONIST ROTATION BY DEPARTMENT",
        "defaultText": "Policy for Internship\n________________\n\n\nPurpose\nThis policy establishes the guidelines, procedures, and standards regulating the Internship Program. It is designed to provide interns with structured learning opportunities while ensuring alignment with the firm’s operation objectives and professional standards.\nObjectives\nThe STLAF Internship Program aims to:\n1. Provide practical and relevant work experience aligned with the intern’s field of study.\n2. Develop the intern’s professional competencies and workplace readiness.\n3. Support departmental functions through supervised participation of interns.\nAssignment and Supervision\n1. All interns shall be directly assigned to a designated leader\n2. The assigned leaders shall be responsible for:\n   1. Providing day-to-day supervision and work instructions\n   2. Monitoring attendance and performance\n   3. Ensuring that tasks assigned are aligned with the intern’s learning objectives and internship plan provided by the firm\n   4. Recommending internship extensions, if applicable\nWork Schedule and Attendance\n1. Interns shall follow the default working hours which is 8:00am to 5:00pm\n2. Attendance must be properly recorded in accordance with procedure of the firm\n3. Any absence or tardiness must be recorded on their DTR and deducted with their daily allowances.\nCode of Conduct\nInterns are required to:\n1. Maintain professionalism and integrity at all times\n2. Comply with all company policies, rules, and regulations\n3. Maintain confidentiality of all company information\n4. Treat all employees, clients and management with respect\nSupervision and Performance Evaluation\n1. Performance shall be monitored by the assigned leader\n2. Feedback shall be provided to support continuous improvement\nAllowance\n1. Interns may be granted a daily allowance of Php 100.00, which shall be released every Monday.\nInternship Extension\nBased on the existing policy of the firm,\n1. Minimum Extension\nInterns requesting an extension must commit to an additional period of at least one (1) week or more.\n2. Increased Daily Allowance\nApproved extensions shall be entitled to the following daily allowance adjustments:\nDURATION\n\tDAILY ALLOWANCE\n\t1 week to 2 weeks only\n\tPhp 100.00 (Default)\n\t1 month and above\n\tPhp 300.00\n\t3. Approval Process\n   1. The assigned leader shall submit an internship program extension request form\n   2. The request must indicate:\n      1. Proposed extension period (start and end dates)\n      2. Justification for the extension\n   3. All requests shall be subject to approval by Management/Partners and the {department}\nCompletion of Internship\n* Interns must complete the required number of hours and assigned deliverables\n* A Certificate of Completion may be issued upon satisfactory completion\nTermination of Internship\nThe firm reserves the right to terminate the internship under the following circumstances:\n1. Violation of company policies, rules or code of conduct\n2. Unsatisfactory performance or failure to meet assigned responsibilities\n3. Habitual tardiness, absenteeism, or abandonment of internship\n4. Misconduct and insubordination\nThe {department} will release a termination letter and provide it to the university or school coordinator.\nInterns may be granted a daily allowance of Php 100.00, which shall be released every Monday."
